subSubSection.paragraph:
Color
. Mostly reddish brown (near 140,53,34) with a few blackish and pale-yellow marks. Lateral patterns in 
Fig. 1
. Mandible blackish except brownish basal spot. Eye margin from level of clypeus to ocelli with narrow paleyellow stripe (
Fig. 2A
). Pronotum anterior margin dorsally widely pale yellow, laterally blackish, apico-ventrally yellow. Mesoscutum on varied areas, propleuron anteriorly, tegula entirely, scutellum lateral spots and apex, mesopleuron ventro-posterior corner, coxae anteriorly and posteriorly, and trochanters mostly, blackish. Femora progressing from yellowish brown (near 140,210,0) on fore leg to reddish brown on hind leg; mid and hind femora ventrally darkest; fore tibia mostly pale yellow, dorsally brown; mid tibia anteriorly pale yellow, otherwise dark brown; hind tibia basal end red brown, remaining dark brown, progressively darker towards apex; fore tarsus progressing from basally light brown to apically dark brown; mid t1–2 whitish, t1 basal 0.1 brown, t3–5 dark brown; hind t1–3 whitish, t4–5 dark brown. Propodeum approximately unicolorous (
Figs 2B, 2D
). Postpetiole and T2–8 progressively dark brown towards apical margin in a somewhat triangular pattern; all tergites with thin border of apical margin pale yellow (
Fig. 2D
); ovipositor laterally flattened, about 3 times taller than narrowest width (near base).
